nderwhelming%2C%20with%20limited%20consumer%20benefits%20and%20unmet%20promises.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHigh%20costs%20and%20technical%20challenges%20hindered%205G's%20widespread%20adoption%20and%20network%20expansion.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EUS%20carriers%20face%20difficulties%20monetizing%205G%2C%20with%20coverage%20gaps%20and%20declining%20revenue%20per%20user.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERemember%20when%205G%20was%20going%20to%20change%20everything%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBack%20in%202019%2C%20wireless%20industry%20leaders%20didn't%20just%20promise%20better%20cell%20service.%20They%20promised%20a%20better%20world%20where%20doctors%20could%20operate%20on%20patients%20remotely%2C%20and%20smart%20cities%20with%20driverless%20cars%20would%20make%20roads%20safer%20and%20less%20congested.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFast%20forward%20to%20today%2C%20and%20the%20average%20consumer%20might%20be%20hard-pressed%20to%20notice%20much%20difference%20between%204G%20and%205G%20in%20their%20daily%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220233a967-3403-44e6-b3c1-15558dc3c378%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Hype%20Machine%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20most%20ambitious%20promises%20either%20didn't%20require%205G%20or%20were%20simply%20impractical.%20For%20instance%2C%20remote%20surgery%20demands%20more%20than%20just%20high-speed%20internet%3B%20it%20requires%20sterile%20environments%2C%20anesthesia%2C%20and%20willing%20patients.%20Similarly%2C%20autonomous%20vehicles%20need%20to%20function%20independently%20of%20a%20mobile%20connection%2C%20raising%20questions%20about%20the%20need%20for%205G%20to%20begin%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20more%20recent%20reports%20mentioning%205G%20take%20a%20different%20tack%20%E2%80%94%20downgrading%20from%20bold%20claims%20like%20ultraconvenient%20%26quot%3Bsmart%20cities%26quot%3B%20to%205G-enabled%20drones%20that%20can%20monitor%20for%20insurance%20fraud.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228e5469c1-9732-4a8f-a004-f611bd21da39%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Technical%20Reality%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20significant%20advancements%20in%205G%20is%20the%20use%20of%20higher%20frequencies%2C%20which%20carry%20more%20information%2C%20but%20don't%20travel%20as%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20to%20use%20them%2C%20you%20need%20more%20antennas%20closer%20together%20%E2%80%94%20something%20called%20network%20densification.%20Building%20out%20the%205G%20network%20in%20the%20US%20has%20required%20hundreds%20of%20billions%20of%20dollars%20of%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20cut%20costs%2C%20much%20of%20the%20early%205G%20infrastructure%20was%20built%20by%20tweaking%20existing%204G%20sites.%20This%20approach%2C%20known%20as%20non-standalone%205G%2C%20offers%20efficiency%20but%20delivers%20a%204G-like%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20thing%20that%20was%20supposed%20to%20be%20really%20different%20about%205G%20was%20the%20introduction%20of%20millimeter%20waves%2C%20which%20can%20theoretically%20provide%20much%20greater%20capacity.%20They%20are%20useful%20in%20select%20locations%20where%20crowds%20really%20pack%20in%20like%20stadiums%20or%20airports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20general%2C%20the%20distance%20they%20travel%20is%20so%20short%20and%20these%20waves%20are%20so%20easily%20blocked%20that%20widespread%20use%20in%20mobile%20networks%20just%20hasn't%20made%20a%20lot%20of%20sense%2C%20and%20many%20smartphones%20don't%20even%20support%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20all%20bad%20news.%20When%20phones%20are%20actually%20connected%20to%20a%205G%20network%2C%20they%20generally%20get%20faster%20speeds%20and%20lower%20latency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20thing%20is%20that%20for%20most%20people%20and%20most%20purposes%2C%20%3Cem%3E4G%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewas%20already%20good%20enough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECoverage%20%E2%80%94%20not%20speed%20%E2%80%94%20is%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20problems%20we%20still%20face.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%225G%20disappointed%20consumers%20and%20phone%20carriers.%20Who's%20cashing%20in%3F%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.jwplayer.com%2Fplayers%2FVHt8tOoB-puACk8ZV.html%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c72e3986-2a40-4ff7-acfc-9af99a0ff74b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Coverage%20Divide%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20coverage%20is%20patchy%20or%20nonexistent%20in%20many%20remote%20or%20rural%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarriers%20simply%20haven't%20built%20their%20networks%20out%20in%20a%20lot%20of%20these%20places%2C%20often%20because%20there%20aren't%20enough%20paying%20customers%20living%20there%20to%20justify%20the%20investment.%20This%20is%20part%20of%20what's%20called%20the%20%26quot%3Bdigital%20divide.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20defining%20feature%20of%205G%20is%20its%20higher%2C%20shorter-range%20frequencies.%20If%20the%20top%20priority%20was%20expanding%20coverage%2C%20building%20out%20existing%204G%20to%20more%20places%20networks%20would%20have%20been%20more%20efficient%20than%20upgrading%20so%20much%20existing%204G%20infrastructure%20in%20cities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you've%20ever%20seen%20a%20TV%20ad%20about%205G%2C%20then%20you%20might%20now%20be%20a%20little%20confused%20because%20the%20maps%20they%20show%20tend%20to%20make%20it%20look%20like%205G%20is%20already%20nearly%20everywhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDouglas%20Dawson%20has%20tested%20cellphone%20speeds%20across%20the%20country%20for%20his%20telecommunication%20consulting%20firm%2C%20CCG%2C%20and%20found%20that%205G%20only%20covers%2030%25%20to%2040%25%20of%20the%20land%20area%20in%20most%20US%20counties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20have%20trouble%20even%20making%20a%20cellphone%20call%20%E2%80%94%204G%20or%205G%20%E2%80%94%20because%20towers%20only%20have%20a%20limited%20circle%20around%20t