E%3Cp%3EThat%20doesn't%20include%20the%20cost%20of%20upgrading%204G%20sites%20to%205G%20or%20of%20building%20tons%20of%20new%20cell%20sites%2C%20which%20has%20required%20billions%20%3Cem%3Emore%20%3C%2Fem%3Edollars%20in%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20they%20have%20struggled%20to%20monetize%205G%2C%20with%20monthly%20phone%20bills%20decreasing%20because%20of%20competition.%20The%20average%20revenue%20per%20user%20has%20been%20trending%20downwards%20even%20as%20investment%20from%20carriers%20has%20risen%2C%20putting%20them%20in%20a%20difficult%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2237f53fea-a0bc-437a-9552-5ebd60f71eca%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Race%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20telecommunications%20is%20of%20massive%20economic%20and%20social%20importance%20equipment%20vendors%20%E2%80%94%20those%20who%20sell%20the%20actual%20infrastructure%20like%20antennas%20%E2%80%94%20and%20industry%20trade%20groups%20can%20lobby%20government%20officials%2C%20telling%20them%20that%20the%20next%20generation%20will%20be%20essential%20and%20transformative%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20if%20they%20don't%20act%20quickly%2C%20they%20might%20miss%20out%20on%20the%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20pressure%20contributed%20to%20the%20narrative%20that%20the%20US%20and%20other%20nations%20were%20engaged%20in%20a%20global%20%26quot%3B5G%20race.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20turn%2C%20politicians%20who%20are%20most%20likely%20not%20telecoms%20engineering%20experts%20but%20might%20also%20be%20eager%20to%20implement%20new%20infrastructure%20projects%20see%20this%20as%20a%20no-risk%20position.%20Who%20wouldn't%20want%20to%20align%20themselves%20with%20the%20next%20frontier%20of%20technological%20innovation%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20rush%20could%20have%20resulted%20in%20many%20of%20these%20problems%2C%20including%20the%20decision%20to%20start%20with%20non-standalone%205G%20networks%2C%20and%20the%20the%20failure%20of%205G%20to%20differentiate%20itself%20from%204G%20in%20the%20eyes%20of%20consumers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%205G%20was%20also%20rushed%20in%20the%20planning%20phase.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeveloping%20a%20plan%20for%20a%20new%20generation%20usually%20takes%20about%2010%20years%2C%20but%205G%20was%20rushed%20out%20in%20just%20eight.%20This%20was%20partially%20because%20of%20global%20political%20pressure%2C%20and%20because%20Japan%20planned%20a%20splashy%205G%20debut%20for%20the%202020%20Olympics%2C%20even%20though%20it%20ended%20up%20delayed%20a%20year%20due%20to%20the%20Covid-19%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2239c4c0f8-16d8-4cdf-bec3-053615c1dcf7%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELooking%20Ahead%3A%206G%20and%20Beyond%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20possible%20that%205G%20will%20be%20a%20continuation%20of%20a%20pattern%20established%20by%20previous%20networks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20odd%20generations%20%E2%80%94%201G%20and%203G%20%E2%80%94%20were%20somewhat%20disappointing%2C%20but%20the%20even%20generations%20that%20followed%20worked%20out%20the%20kinks%20and%20had%20greater%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20we%20could%20see%20bigger%20transformations%20with%206G.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20we%20get%20closer%20to%20the%20sixth%20generation%2C%20most%20experts%20Business%20Insider%20spoke%20to%20said%20it's%20on%20the%20same%20troubled%20path.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-5g-failed-to-change-the-world-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743022985000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67e4670e69253ccddf9a659f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-5g-failed-to-change-the-world-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20rollout%20of%205G%20faced%20high%20costs%20and%20technical%20challenges%2C%20leading%20to%20unmet%20promises%20and%20limited%20consumer%20benefits%2C%20as%20US%20coverage%20gaps%20persist.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ins